A Model who has box geometry link does not spawned, when \\<size\\> tag’s value in \\<box\\> geometry has white space at the front.

Example

```xml
&lt;?xml version=&#34;1.0&#34; ?&gt;
&lt;sdf version=&#34;1.4&#34;&gt;
    &lt;model name=&#39;a_model&#39;&gt;
        &lt;link name=&#39;box_shape_linnk&#39;&gt;
            &lt;pose&gt; 0 0 0 0 0 0 &lt;/pose&gt;
            &lt;collision name=&#39;col_box&#39;&gt;
                &lt;geometry&gt;
                    &lt;box&gt;
                        &lt;size&gt; 1 1 1 &lt;/size&gt;
                    &lt;/box&gt;
                &lt;/geometry&gt;
            &lt;/collision&gt;
            &lt;visual name=&#39;vis_box&#39;&gt;
                &lt;geometry&gt;
                    &lt;box&gt;
                        &lt;size&gt; 1 1 1 &lt;/size&gt; &lt;!-- size value has whitespace at the front--&gt;
                    &lt;/box&gt;
                &lt;/geometry&gt;
            &lt;/visual&gt;
        &lt;/link&gt;
    &lt;/model&gt;
&lt;/sdf&gt;
```

Because before parse the value of \\<size\\> tag, value string is splited to \\\[“ “,  size\_x, , size\_y, size\_z, “ “\\\] when value string contain white space at front.

It occurs when parseSize function split ‘sizeStr’ with &amp;#39;\\s\+&amp;#39; regex.

So when trim\(\) was added to remove the space, it was confirmed that the model with the box size containing front of white space could be spawned

```javascript
---  var values = sizeStr.split(/\s+/); 
+++  var values = sizeStr.trim().split(/\s+/);  
```

